Partly cloudy- breezy.  Some boats.  Water skiier.
Calm- clear- lake level extremely low (no rain for weeks)
Breezy- lake level extremely low (no rain for weeks)
Windy- clear- warm (lake level up 4" from low point).
Cloudy and breezy - observed a deer swimming and male loons away from their nests
clear- breezy - winds from the northwest clear- sunny- northwest breeze

Calm- sunny - Susan McKinney also helped. Flow of water from many unusual locations continued into the lake as an abundance of rain fell 2 days earlier. Sunny- calm and water continued to flow in from unusual places as heavy rains took place on 8/20. Susan McKinney assisted in the data recording.
Clear- calm day air temperature approximately 50 degrees. Clear- sunny air temperature approximately 50 degrees
Partly cloudly- lots of pollen on the surface. Partly cloudy- lots of pollen on the surface.
partly cloudy calm day following a day that had a violent but brief passing storm
Mostly overcast- no wind- air temp 47 degrees. Observed a smew merganser.
Cloudy- cool + breezy. Cloudy- cool + breezy. Cloudy- cool + breezy.
partly cloudy + breezy. partly cloudy + breezy. partly cloudy + breezy.
cloudy with a steady wind from the east.
cloudy with a steady wind from the east. cloudy with a strong east wind. cloudy with a strong east wind.
overcast + calm (storm the night before with high winds)
overcast + calm (strong stroms the night before with high winds)
Hot- hazy- humid and calm. Hot- hazy- humid + calm.  Hot- hazy- humid + calm.
mostly- cloudy and breeze coming from the north.
Breezy- sunny and clear. Spotted 2 adult loons swimming/fishing along the north shore.
clear early morning a day and a half after a major storm
clear- steady northwesterly wind - Monday following moderately busy- recreational boating weekend.
Day of clearing after 3 days of consistent rainfall. Wind NW at 12 mph.
Sample taken in between rain drops and following several days of rain and storms.
beautiful clear cool day- low humidity and light northeasterly winds
calm- clear day - slight NE breeze
calm- clear day with increasing temperatures
Partly cloudy day with a cold 8 mph wind from the north. Measureable rainfall + major cold front began to move in 40 hours prior to sampling.
clear to partly cloudy- slight breeze
cloudy- NW wind 5 mph. Loon pair with twins.
Partly cloudy wind from the N at 10 mph. Loon family with 2 chicks and an eagle were spotted.
